SIMPLE: indecency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indecency
<hw>In*de"cen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Indecencies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>indecentia</ets> unseemliness: cf. F.
<ets>ind⟦eacute⟧cence</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being indecent; lack of
decency, modesty, or good manners; obscenity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is indecent; an indecent word or act; an
offense against delicacy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They who, by speech or writing, present to the ear or the eye of
modesty any of the <qex>indecencies</qex> I allude to, are pests of
society.</q> <rj><qau>Beattie.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Indelicacy; indecorum; immodesty; impurity;
obscenity. See <er>Indecorum</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indecent</ent>⟦br⟧
